body:
when the source used in a channel volume is finite the channel volume returns too early by one sample and also may return some Some(sample) after the None.

This behavior is not handled correctly by UniformSourceIterator which can never end.
The following example failed to end:
```rust
extern crate rodio;

use std::io::BufReader;
use rodio::Source;

fn main() {
    let source = ::rodio::buffer::SamplesBuffer::new(1, 44100, vec![1i16, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6]);
    let source = ::rodio::source::ChannelVolume::new(source, vec![0.5, 0.5]);
    let source = rodio::source::UniformSourceIterator::<_, i16>::new(source, 2, 44100);

    // runs forever
    let output = source.collect::<Vec<_>>();
}
```

the current implementation ensure that samples for output channels are None when every channel in its source are None.

This may (should?) fix the issue #120 

But the UniformSourceIterator could still never ends for weird input but at least channelVolume doesn't output that anymore.

The issue could also be fixed with something more like a fuse but I think the current implementation is OK and logical.

And I can add the test in the PR if you want to.

Thank you
